			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think you're almost right, Andric.  You can remain invisible while having aggro <b>if you are out of aggro range of the hostile mob</b>.  In the scenario you described, I assume you had Selos and hot-footed it out of aggro range so your invis was fine.  As soon as that mob gets into aggro range though, you will not be invis.  At least that has been my experience through the years.</span></td>
